#Reviewed the string comparison challenge with the houseplant input
#Realized that the comparison variables don't have to be global
#This is the more streamlined code. Probably not necessary to put in this git but,
#did not want to forget that there's yet another way to do it.

plant = input("Please enter the name of a houseplant: ")

if plant == "Spathipyllum" :
    print("Yes! - Spathiphyllum is the best plant ever.")

elif plant == "spathiphyllum" :
    print("No! I want a BIG Spathiphyllum!")
    
else:
    print("Spathiyphyllum! Not "+ plant + "!" )
